NAME: l-1
DESCRIPTION: per litre; example plankton counts or grams per litre; phyto often expressed as cells per litre

NAME: C chl-1 h-1 W-1 m-2
DESCRIPTION: mg C / (mg chl_a * hour * watt * square metre )

NAME: o/oo SMOW
DESCRIPTION: parts / thousand, relative to Standard Mean Ocean Water (SMOW)

NAME: mg C/m**3/h
DESCRIPTION: milligrams carbon per cubic metre per hour

NAME: (mg C m-2hr-1)/I0
DESCRIPTION: PP normalized to incident radiation (mg C m-2 hr-1) / (cal m-2 hr-1)

NAME: (mg C m-2hr-1)/I0Bz
DESCRIPTION: PP normalized to incident radiation and phyto biomass(mg C m-2 hr-1) / ((cal m-2 hr-1)(mg Chla m-2))

NAME: cal / g dry wt
DESCRIPTION: calories per gram of dry weight

NAME: Micrometer
DESCRIPTION: Microscope units, conversion to mm depends upon the ocular power of the microscope.

NAME: eggs fem-1 day-1
DESCRIPTION: rate measurement - number of eggs produced by an individual female per day

NAME: mL-1
DESCRIPTION: per millilitre; example plankton counts or grams per mL; bacteria often expressed as cells per mL

NAME: NTU
DESCRIPTION: Nephelometric turbidity units - measurement of turbidity

NAME: m-1 sr-1
DESCRIPTION: per m per steradian for turbidity measurements
